-- Capitals’ Erskine Suspended for 3 Games Over Elbowing, NHL Says
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2013-02-03T05:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-03/capitals-erskine-suspended-for-3-games-over-elbowing-nhl-says.html
Washington Capitals defenseman John Erskine was suspended for three games for elbowing  Philadelphia
Flyers  forward Wayne Simmonds, the National Hockey League said.  Erskine will forfeit $24,324.33 under terms of the
Collective Bargaining Agreement, the league said. The money will
be turned over to the Players’ Emergency Assistance Fund.  Erskine elbowed Simmonds at 18:09 of the first period on
the Capitals’ home ice on Feb. 1, the league said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  